channel.title: Need Help Please!
channel.description:
Well basically as I see it. I'm never going to be able to host a RSPS again.
It will not let me host for some reason. I'm not sure if it is my IP or what I did with portfoward.
If you can help me and have Team Viewer PM me please!!!!!!!!!

item.title: Need Help Please!
item.dc:creator: @whattehp406 whattehp406
item.description:
@whattehp406 wrote:

[quote="…::Tech::…, post:15, topic:415346"][quote author=whattehp406 link=topic=517304.msg3757731#msg3757731 date=1316623146]
Double check your Portforwarding, make sure it’s directed to your current computer ip. (use ipconfig to find out the ip)
If the port is open and your server is running succesfully try looking into your client. Go to http://canyouseeme.org/ to check if your port is truely open.
If that also doesn’t work call your ISP and ask if they blocked port 43594.
[/quote]

Thanks for the help. (Unlike everyone who is making this a flame thread)

I’ll see if what you suggested works. Hopefully it does because i promised that I’d have it back up in a couple of days.[/quote]No problem.
